EPBT is defined as the time required for the solar PV system to generate the same amount of energy used in its entire life cycle. The formula for calculating the same is given by Eq. 1.
1EPBTyears=CEDEagen/ηG−EO&M\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ EPBT\ \left(\mathrm{years}\right)=\frac{CED}{\left({E}_{agen}/{\eta}_G\right)-{E}_{O\&M}} $$\end{document}

ii) Eagen: Annual electricity generation, given by Eq. 22Eagen=irradiation×performance ratio×module efficiency\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
